                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Child</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-04T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Your despatch No. 192, January 30.</p>
                <p>You will ask the Italian Government whether it will not now abandon its
                    reservation to the arms declaration of May 5, 1919, in view of the disastrous
                    effect which the maintenance of such a reservation <pb facs="0848" n="728"
                        xml:id="pg_728"/> and the consequent further delivery of munitions to
                    contending factions in China may have.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
